Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.57,0:00:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Following the murder of design company president\NWakamatsu Kouhei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in his villa in Karuizawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.87,0:00:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His son Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was poisoned to death in his Tokyo residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.29,0:00:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bizarrely, the poison was not found anywhere else other\Nthan on the piece of baumkuchen that Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.21,0:00:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what method did the culprit use to poison Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.09,0:00:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the tiles in the bathroom where president\NWakamatsu was murdered were so-called Crazy Diamonds...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.27,0:00:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whose patterns would have induced an\Noptical illusion, and were noticed by...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.23,0:00:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagano Police Inspector Yamato Kansuke and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.17,0:00:40.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They managed to reconstruct the missing dying\Nmessage left by president Wakamatsu, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.03,0:00:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had three letters of the alphabet...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.53,0:00:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"S-O-N!"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.83,0:00:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Son...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.78,0:00:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His son?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.09,0:01:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If all cases were men.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.79,0:01:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose the invisible mysteries would be women.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.64,0:01:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We now have the mysteries behind the Crazy\NDiamonds and the newfound poison trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.97,0:01:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.59,0:01:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect o an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.57,0:01:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.11,0:02:51.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,THE DESIGN OF POISON AND MIRAGE
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.11,0:02:51.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,(POISON)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.35,0:02:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.17,0:02:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the one who was murdered tonight in Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the son of the company president who was\Nmurdered here at this villa in Karuizawa a month ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.61,0:03:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the culprit deliberately left those\Nletters in order to place the blame on the son?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that were the case, it should have been\Nleft in a manner much easier to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.58,0:03:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit would not have gone through the trouble to\Nuse the Crazy Diamonds illusion to hide the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.46,0:03:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, there's a strong indicator that hatred was involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing that the son was the.one who murdered the president...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.43,0:03:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be appropriate to surmise that the culprit took revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.89,0:03:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we can't rule out an accomplice\Nwho did it to silence him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.73,0:03:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being that the message was only "Son",\Nit would-be apt to consider it a solo crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.52,0:03:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we're going through the trouble of giving\Nyou this info, try not to let another victim turn up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.25,0:03:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means, the one who deliberately called\Nus to the president's family home in Osaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.80,0:03:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And showed us the trick of the disappearing letters...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.39,0:04:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might be the culprit this time, the one\Nwho murdered the son, Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.88,0:04:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.24,0:04:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they had wanted to tell us to hurry up\Nf and figure out the Crazy Diamonds illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.03,0:04:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, being the culprit himself,\Nwouldn't have given such a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.04,0:04:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the question is, why did the president's wife hide the fact that\Nthe tiles in this bathroom were the same as the ones in the villa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.18,0:04:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit had wanted the Crazy Diamonds to be noticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.76,0:04:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it means the mistress had tried to work against their cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.62,0:04:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.20,0:04:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't your manner of speaking different from before?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.95,0:04:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because when you were with everyone\Nyou spoke normally like a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.45,0:04:38.04,Signs,,0,0,0,,Vonehara Sakurako (23)\NHouskeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.55,0:04:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now it's almost as if you're a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.87,0:04:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He s just playing pretend!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm just here to watch over this brat's play-detective game!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.97,0:04:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Little boy, you can't get in the way of the investigations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.15,0:04:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this big brother here is an\Nextremely capable high-school detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.99,0:04:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fi-i-ine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But had the president been talking about me like that to everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.08,0:05:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and all the time too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying "How nice it'd be if only I had\Na son like Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} to be my heir...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why, as far as my son is concerned, is he so inept?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.41,0:05:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as his son is concerned?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.75,0:05:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So did he have any daughters?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.10,0:05:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.93,0:05:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he just meant in comparison to Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.82,0:05:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would like to confirm once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ate the poisoned baumkuchen and collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You all were in your current positions, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.50,0:05:39.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.91,0:05:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Housekeeper!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.39,0:05:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.09,0:05:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.51,0:05:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was right about where you are now, Inspector,\Nholding the tray with the baumkuchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.07,0:05:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're too loud!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.68,0:05:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who murdered the president was his son, Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.53,0:05:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.68,0:06:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because everyone thinks that in the president's\Nand Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.90,0:06:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same person who held a grudge against\Nboth of them was the culprit right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.28,0:06:11.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, isn't it better to keep this a secret for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.45,0:06:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.87,0:06:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that the culprit of this case had a different\Nmotive than the one from the president's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.22,0:06:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They may have a grudge against whoever murdered the president
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.83,0:06:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Detective Takagi, ask everyone on the sly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.96,0:06:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Specifically, whether there was anyone\Nwho really loved the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.18,0:06:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to keep this a secret from the inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.14,0:06:34.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To fool your enemies you must first fool your allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.30,0:06:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Heiji, I wonder what he's whispering to Detective Takagi about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.98,0:06:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.26,0:06:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking.of which, what was that earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.29,0:06:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said there was something you had to tell me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.65,0:06:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not really the right time to say this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.45,0:06:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,KUDOU-KUN DID!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:02.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.04,0:07:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't mind us...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.95,0:07:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.17,0:07:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you girls gossiping about at a crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.82,0:07:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, with the exception of Satake{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?and\NYonehara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, none of you touched the baumkuchen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.33,0:07:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} really confess his feelings to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.65,0:07:23.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A while ago, I went to London on a trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.82,0:07:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi happened to be there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.46,0:07:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And suddenly, in front of Big Ben...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.42,0:07:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dashing, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.99,0:07:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dashing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.38,0:07:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's so romantic!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.31,0:07:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.54,0:07:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened afterwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.37,0:07:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.87,0:07:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.16,0:07:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you two probably met up and called each other, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.21,0:07:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.71,0:07:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In particular...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you should give him a call!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.01,0:07:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I kind of feel like I forced him into confessing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.68,0:07:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.01,0:08:00.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I kind of want to hold on to this happy\Nfeeling for just a little while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.93,0:08:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get the feeling that if I call him...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.44,0:08:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,lill end up crashing back to reality from this dream-like event.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too naive, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.78,0:08:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've already pushed him to the edge of the\Nring and he's wavin' the white flag, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.53,0:08:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why won't you give that one final push and claim the victory!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.67,0:08:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Victory," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll also gather up my courage and confess to Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.85,0:08:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you'll also brave up and confirm\Nwith Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} whether it was a dream or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.31,0:08:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.88,0:08:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.93,0:08:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What've you been chattering about this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.72,0:08:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in an on-the-spot investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.52,0:08:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we're in an investigation meeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please not interrupt our conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.91,0:08:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.65,0:08:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.45,0:08:55.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.86,0:08:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s sake, I have to show her how it's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.33,0:09:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.82,0:09:06.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.04,0:09:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.17,0:09:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's she glarin' at me for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.41,0:09:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.23,0:09:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is no point in doing this any further, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.55,0:09:15.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shiina Masashige (56)\NSenior Managing Director
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.22,0:09:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.42,0:09:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question isn't where everyone was\Nstanding at the time of the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.84,0:09:19.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,Fujinami Sumio (30)\NChief Designer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's how that idiot son was made to take the poisoned\Nbaumkuchen piece between the two, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that mystery isn't solved, no matter how much\Nyou conduct this on-the-site inspection...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.77,0:09:36.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,Satake Yoshimi (32)\NSecretary
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.98,0:09:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't an on-the-site inspection, but a\Nvoluntarily conducted on-the-spot investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For an on-the-site inspection, you would need\Nto have a court-issued warrant in hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And present it to us before commencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.02,0:09:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that you could make us take in the meaning of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have in hand before commencing"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make someone take in"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.83,0:09:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.17,0:09:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kind of trick is still possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.35,0:09:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.14,0:10:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm borrowing the housekeeper again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.47,0:10:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, we're borrowing the forensics officer outside too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but do pass on the word.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.40,0:10:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, doing as they please...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.65,0:10:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's positive?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.15,0:10:19.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, powdered poison was sprinkled over the doorknob.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.61,0:10:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt this was Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.73,0:10:25.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.57,0:10:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would poison be at a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.79,0:10:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't happen to choose the\Npoisoned piece of baumkuchen out of the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.41,0:10:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before he took it the poison was already on his hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.61,0:10:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He already had it from when he left this room\Nand grabbed the knob to close the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:47.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, for Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who always\Neats cakes and things using his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter which baumkuchen slice he took,\Nhe would've taken in the poison anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.86,0:10:54.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.52,0:10:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question is who put the poison on the doorknob.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is there poison on the floor too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:05.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.28,0:11:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In between the boards.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.04,0:11:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be there is about a ten-centimeter\Nhollow in that powdered poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.79,0:11:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.24,0:11:17.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's an open gap about that large in\Nthe poison found in between the boards.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.64,0:11:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.35,0:11:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this, as to who applied the poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.93,0:11:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be possible to find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.93,0:11:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.06,0:11:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd like to investigate their slippers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.94,0:11:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What've you been up to this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.15,0:11:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in the middle of questioning!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.36,0:11:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is important!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.24,0:11:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, we'll take yours and the others' too, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.61,0:11:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from those of you waiting in line outside the room as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.75,0:11:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put the slippers you have on now into\Nthe bags marked with your name!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.90,0:12:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, you have no clues as far as anyone who possesses\Na particular grudge against the president or Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.62,0:12:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.76,0:12:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care about the son...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.76,0:12:08.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure everyone liked the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.60,0:12:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the president was a workaholic\Nto the point of ignoring his family...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.26,0:12:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was divorced twice as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.56,0:12:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Divorced twice, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.16,0:12:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, on the other hand, anyone who\Nparticularly loved the president?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.94,0:12:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not who particularly hated him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.95,0:12:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, for reference purposes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.47,0:12:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that'd be Director Shiina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.36,0:12:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they've been together since the company started.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.25,0:12:38.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.21,0:12:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president and I were colleagues\Nin college, and we go back a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few years ago, to celebrate my 30 years of continuous\Nservice, he even gifted me a bronze fountain pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.57,0:12:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.68,0:12:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fountain pen you lent the mistress earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.17,0:12:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.06,0:13:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe he gave each of the other\Nemployees a bronze wristwatch instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.54,0:13:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, was there anyone who loved\Nthe president more than yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.77,0:13:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably the secretary, Satake{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.33,0:13:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was so devoted to him, to the point\Nhis previous wife would even get jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.32,0:13:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a secretary, isn't it only natural to\Nbe devoted to the company president?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.47,0:13:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how is this question related to anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.68,0:13:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just to know how well-loved the president was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.18,0:13:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I suppose the housekeeper\NYonehara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r} would be the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.22,0:13:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, her mother was also a,housekeeper for this household.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.98,0:13:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her mother was a single mother who died of an illness and left\Nher without any means, but he took her in as his own child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.07,0:13:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And afterwards, he employed her as his housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:49.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.99,0:13:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am so grateful to the master that I cannot thank him enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even paid for my tuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.33,0:14:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, probably the Chief Designer\NFujinami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would rank the highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.49,0:14:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That crude mouth of his caused him to have\Ngotten fired from many different companies...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.72,0:14:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the master expressed faith in his\Ntalent and took him in, or so I was told.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.27,0:14:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even-at the master's funeral, that\Nperson was the one who cried the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.57,0:14:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.41,0:14:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mistress, aren't you in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.44,0:14:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your slippers are the only ones untested!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.59,0:14:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone else's slippers didn't test positive for poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.19,0:14:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The powdered poison would get on the slippers...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.40,0:14:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the culprit sprinkled the poison on Ikurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s doorknob.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.15,0:14:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the poison would also fall on\Nthe slippers the culprit was wearing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.25,0:14:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a gap about ten-centimeters wide\Nin the poison on the floor under the knob.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.17,0:14:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means, if we inspect your slippers,\Nwe'll find out that you're the culpri-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.36,0:15:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan Episode 654\NFansub Release by DCTP\NRipped by DJ VK & Innushka
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.33,0:15:05.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.36,0:15:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.87,0:15:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death was a cyanide based poison again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.53,0:15:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.50,0:15:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wouldn't this be a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.27,0:15:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we all left this study, the last one to\Nclose the door was the Inspector, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.64,0:15:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The vice-president was still alive then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the first ones to open the door to this\Nroom under police surveillance...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.53,0:15:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were the Osaka detective brats who\Nfound the vice-president's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.78,0:15:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then there's no way it wasn't a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.49,0:15:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.69,0:15:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was a murder, it would be a sealed-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.96,0:15:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means it'd have to be an impossible crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.50,0:15:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's certainly so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.44,0:15:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say it's impossible, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.22,0:15:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, there are all sorts of suspicious\Nthings on top of this desk here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.84,0:16:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The black tea brought by Housekeeper\NYonehara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has been partially sipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fountain pen Director Shiina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nlent to the mistress has its tip left out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.19,0:16:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the cap attached to its rear end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.15,0:16:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the contract that Secretary Satake{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked the\Nmistress to sign and stamp, she had started to work on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.53,0:16:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the eye drops that the mistress-received\Nfrom Chief Designer Fujinami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.01,0:16:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have been removed from the box and looks like some was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.70,0:16:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think they're strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.69,0:16:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.39,0:16:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If something from the desk was used in a clever way..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.17,0:16:35.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would mean that someone could have poisoned the\Nmistress to death even if they weren't in this study!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that thick Japanese dictionary that had fallen to the ground\Nnext to the mistress along with its case are also quite suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.10,0:16:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to have been opened to the "Wa" entry page.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.93,0:16:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the circumstances...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.55,0:16:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly probable that she.came into contact with the\Npoison as she was looking something up in this dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, if there was a kanji character\Nshe couldn't read, and wanted to look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.32,0:17:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means, the contract the mistress\Nwas asked to sign and stamp, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.45,0:17:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The instruction guide on the eye drops would be fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.21,0:17:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.29,0:17:14.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit knowing that there would be\Ndifficult-to-read kanji characters or words in the text...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.84,0:17:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely induced the.mistress to grab\Nthe poison-laced Japanese dictionary!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.76,0:17:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.39,0:17:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure there aren't any kanji the vice-president can't read.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.47,0:17:27.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The vice-president passed the Level 1 kanji aptitude test.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.52,0:17:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.98,0:17:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you save your suspicion of us until after you have read the\Nvice-president's sealed letter she had placed in safekeeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.61,0:17:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sealed letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.23,0:17:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was asked by the vice-president
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.95,0:17:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That if anything were to happen to her, I was\Nto present that sealed letter to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.04,0:17:49.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sealed letter was stored inside the house safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of the letter was the mistress's written confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.92,0:17:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the villa in Karuizawa, when she rushed to the bathroom\Nafter hearing about how the,president had been stabbed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.42,0:18:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth was the son had been hiding behind\Nthe door, blood-stained with a knife in hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without thinking, she ended up covering for him, and\Nthat was written in the mistress own handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.64,0:18:15.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason she covered for him was because her son had caught\Nwind of the fact that she was the one embezzling company funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.65,0:18:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And before the police arrived, she manufactured traces of\Nit having been an outside crime and hid the weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.87,0:18:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And disposed of it afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.08,0:18:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She also made use of an optical illusion to\Nhide the president's dying message, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.50,0:18:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She feared that her son would someday murder her\Nin order to silence her knowledge of the crime
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.97,0:18:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that were to happen, she would like that dying message\Nsubmitted to the police as a piece of evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.33,0:18:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with that sentence, the written confession ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.68,0:18:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the only one to know of the existence\Nof this sealed letter you, the secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.02,0:18:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:19:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems the vice-president opened the safe every\Nnight in order to check that the seal had not been broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So perhaps the others may have found it odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.24,0:19:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also thought the mistress had been hiding something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.87,0:19:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because when I came into this room to do some\Ncleaning, I found the mistress in front of the safe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.62,0:19:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yelling, "Knock the door before entering the room!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.84,0:19:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And got extremely upset with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.87,0:19:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But about that, I think the others may have noticed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.64,0:19:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the mistress often invited the company\Npersonnel over to this house for conferences.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.10,0:19:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, you all at least had some inkling\Nof this sealed letter's existence, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.98,0:19:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.23,0:19:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Traces of poison were found on the mistress's slippers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.39,0:19:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.57,0:19:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that it was the mistress who sprinkled\Npowdered poison on the doorknob of the son's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.18,0:19:56.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some poison remained in between the\Nfloorboards under that doorknob...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.17,0:20:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the width of the interval in between matched\Nup with the width of the poison on the slipper.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.92,0:20:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unable to withstand the threat of possibly being murdered by the\Nson, the mistress taking the first.move was what happened here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noway...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.77,0:20:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That certainly is plausible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.35,0:20:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite impossible for the culprit to have made someone else\Nexchange their own slippers for the ones with poison, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.64,0:20:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, the Japanese dictionary on the ground next\Nto the mistress's body also tested positive for poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.45,0:20:32.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The poison was only at a spot to the\Nbottom left of the fore edge of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.49,0:20:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But deep inside the case in which the dictionary was housed,\Na packet with poison had been affixed, and was slightly torn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.50,0:20:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it may be that someone had hidden the poison\Nthere, and by some circumstance the packet tore...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.42,0:20:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unwittingly getting poison onto that part of the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.43,0:20:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means, the person who hid\Nit there may have been the mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.18,0:20:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:21:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After poisoning the son, she concealed the packet of poison there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if he was the president's son from\Nanother marriage, he was still her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.82,0:21:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thus, tormented by the feeling of regret for having killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's plausible that she may have taken the poison that came out\Nfrom the packet, and put it into her mouth to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.41,0:21:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, the mistress's non-participation\Nin the on-the-spot investigation was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.12,0:21:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because she wanted to be alone, having\Nalready decided to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.37,0:21:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, so nothing came from the things\Non top of the desk in this study?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.51,0:21:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No poison was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.72,0:21:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And neither the contract nor the instructions for the\Neye drops contained any particularly difficult kanji.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.55,0:21:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who was the one who called me to\Nthe president's family home in Osaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.39,0:21:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wanted me to figure out the Crazy Diamonds illusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.86,0:21:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe the mistress was using you in order to test you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.07,0:21:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking that if you, who was deemed by the\Npresident as a skilled detective, couldn't figure it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.91,0:21:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the optical illusion trick would never come to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.41,0:22:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never in her wildest dreams could she have imagined that you\Nwould bring along yours truly, a genuine great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.34,0:22:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, are you saying she deliberately decided to\Ncommit a murder in front of such a great detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.56,0:22:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How should I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.13,0:22:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she'd already set up the poison and\Ncouldn't forestall it after the fact, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.26,0:22:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What ever the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.89,0:22:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you've decided that the vice-president\Nis the culprit could we go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.54,0:22:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last train will be leaving soon, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.18,0:22:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I must return home and discuss with my wife regarding the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.32,0:22:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll stick with the investigation as long as it takes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.81,0:22:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we do wish to hear from you all regarding\Nthe mistress's state of mind before she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.66,0:22:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please bear with the investigation for just a short while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.17,0:24:24.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.14,0:24:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This talk about baumkuchen makes me\Nwant to eat some half-moon fish cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.21,0:24:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.38,0:24:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was "an eye for an eye"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.21,0:24:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, how'd the culprit make that\Nidiot son take the poisoned baumkuchen?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.51,0:24:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{text from 655}Then why don't you try taking one, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.92,0:24:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So pretend[you're lkurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who's starving to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.04,0:24:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I'm starving, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.36,0:24:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.40,0:24:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,THE DESIGN OF POISON AND MIRAGE\N(ILLUSION)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.69,0:24:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.97,0:24:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wristwatch
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.19,0:24:54.69,Adds,,0,0,0,,Look Forward to the Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.39,0:24:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today (5\5) is Boys' Day!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.44,0:24:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, how old are you now after yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.60,0:24:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A secret...
